        'slug' => 'tibiao-whitewater-kayak-antique-river-trip-slow-read',
        'excerpt' => 'The Tibiao River in Antique is the only commercial whitewater kayak run in the Visayas. Here is the trip read, the rapids, and the Panay coastal drive.',
        'content_html' => <<<'HTML'
<p>The Tibiao River runs from the Madja-as mountain range down through the town of Tibiao in Antique province, on the west side of Panay Island. The upper section of the river holds Class II and Class III rapids in the wet months, which is rare in the Visayas. Tibiao is the only commercial whitewater kayak operation in the region, run by the local tourism office and the Kawa Hot Bath complex. Tara, here is the slow read for the river trip.</p>
<p>The standard plan is a morning kayak run, an afternoon Kawa hot bath, and a sunset stop at the Tibiao river beach. Combine with the Tuburan Seven Falls trek the next day for a full Antique outdoor weekend.</p>
<h2>The Kayak Run</h2>
<p>The run starts at Brgy. Tuno upstream, with a short orientation and a fitting for the helmet, life vest, and paddle. The kayaks are single-seat inflatables, easy to handle and forgiving on the rapids. The local guides ride alongside in their own boats and call out the lines through the rapids.</p>
<h3>The Class II and III Sections</h3>
<p>The first kilometer is flat water with the current pushing you along. The middle section drops into a series of small rapids, around six in a row, that the local guides call by the names the families on the river use for them. The Class III sections are tight curves with standing waves; the lines are easy to follow if you keep the bow pointed downstream.</p>
<h3>The Calm Lower Section</h3>
<p>The last kilometer is calmer water, suitable for swimming next to the kayak. The river opens into a wider channel with banks of river-rocks and small sandy patches. The take-out is at the Tibiao Kawa Hot Bath complex, where the rental crew helps you out of the kayak and walks you to the changing area.</p>
<h2>The Kawa Hot Bath</h2>
<p>The Kawa Hot Bath is the Tibiao signature, a wooden vat of warm water heated by a small wood fire beneath. The water has lemongrass, ginger, and herbs floating in it. The bath sits next to the river, you soak with the river sound in the background. After the kayak trip, the warm soak is the kind of recovery routine that turns a Tibiao day into a return trip.</p>
<h2>What to Bring</h2>
<ul>
<li>Quick-dry shirt and shorts you do not mind getting wet</li>
<li>Aqua shoes that grip wet rocks</li>
<li>Dry bag for the phone and wallet</li>
<li>Sunscreen, the lower river is open sun</li>
<li>Light long-sleeve sun shirt</li>
<li>Cash for the kayak rental, the Kawa, and the guide tip</li>
<li>A towel and a change of clothes</li>
</ul>
<h2>Getting to Tibiao</h2>
<p>Fly to Caticlan or Iloilo, the two closest airports. From Caticlan, the drive south through Pandan, Sebaste, and into Tibiao is around three hours. From Iloilo, the drive north through San Jose and into Tibiao is around four and a half hours. <a href="https://www.cebupacificair.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">Cebu Pacific</a> serves both airports daily. Bus or van transfers from either airport are available.</p>
<h2>When to Go</h2>
<p>The whitewater season is the wet months from July to October when the river runs at the higher levels. The Class III sections need rainfall to be runnable. November to May the river drops, the rapids become Class I and II only, and the trip is more of a flat-water kayak. The Kawa Hot Bath runs year-round. The wet-season trip has a higher cancel risk during typhoons; check the local tourism office two days before the trip.</p>
<h2>Where to Stay</h2>
<p>Tibiao has small farm stays and the Kawa complex itself has rustic rooms. For broader options, the town of Culasi to the north has a few inns near the boat ports for Mararison Island. Compare options on <a href="https://www.tripadvisor.com.ph/Hotels-g3895061-Antique_Province_Western_Visayas_Visayas-Hotels.html" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">TripAdvisor PH</a>.</p>
<p>Tibiao is the rare outdoor stop in the Visayas where the river, the soak, and the food all sit within a 10-minute drive of each other. For travelers who want kayak time without going to Cagayan de Oro or Davao, the Tibiao run is the closer call. Pair it with the Tuburan trek and the Mararison sandbar and the Antique weekend writes itself.</p>
HTML,
        'meta_title' => 'Tibiao Whitewater Kayak, Antique: River Trip Plan | Resort Guru PH',
        'meta_description' => 'A DIY plan for the Tibiao River kayak run in Antique. Rapids notes, Kawa Hot Bath stop, transport from Caticlan or Iloilo, and best months.',
        'tags' => 'Tibiao, Antique, Whitewater Kayak, Kawa Hot Bath, Panay',
