    // ------------------------------------------------------------------
    // 16. TUBURAN SEVEN FALLS TREK, TIBIAO ANTIQUE
    // ------------------------------------------------------------------
    [
        'source_url' => 'https://www.thetraveljunkie.org/tibiao-bugtong-bato-falls/',
        'source_blog_name' => 'The Travel Junkie',
        'source_image_url' => null,
        'title' => 'Tuburan and Bugtong Bato Seven Falls Trek: A Tibiao Climb',
        'slug' => 'tuburan-bugtong-bato-seven-falls-trek-tibiao-climb',
        'excerpt' => 'The Tuburan and Bugtong Bato Falls in Tibiao, Antique are a seven-tier waterfall trek into the Madja-as foothills. Here is the trail plan and the falls order.',
        'content_html' => <<<'HTML'
<p>Above the Tibiao Kawa complex, the Madja-as foothills hold the Tuburan and Bugtong Bato Falls system, a series of seven cascades along a single river. The standard trek climbs to the third or fourth falls, depending on the group fitness; the higher falls are the technical part of the trip with fixed-rope sections and rock scrambles. Most groups stop at the third falls, swim in the wide pool, and turn back. Strong trekkers can push to the seventh.</p>
<p>The trek is around three hours up to the third falls, four hours back including swim stops. Combine with the Tibiao kayak the day before for a full outdoor weekend in Antique.</p>
<h2>The Trail in Brief</h2>
<p>The jump-off is at Brgy. Tuno in Tibiao, a 15-minute tricycle ride from the Kawa Hot Bath complex. Register at the barangay tourism table, hire a local guide, and start the climb on a coconut grove farm road. The first 30 minutes is open farm with a few river crossings on bamboo bridges.</p>
<h3>First Falls</h3>
<p>The first falls is around 30 minutes from the jump-off, a wide cascade into a calm pool. The local kids swim here in the afternoons. Stop for a photo and push on, the higher falls are the real highlight.</p>
<h3>Second Falls</h3>
<p>The second falls is another 30 minutes up, narrower and taller than the first, with a deeper pool. The trail to it has a few rock-hopping sections across the river. Most family groups turn back here.</p>
<h3>Third Falls</h3>
<p>The third falls is the standard stopping point for active trekkers. The cascade is around 25 meters tall, with a wide circular pool at the base that is around 4 meters deep at the center. Swim across, sit on the rocks behind the falling water, eat the packed lunch.</p>
<h3>Fourth Through Seventh Falls</h3>
<p>The fourth falls and above require fixed-rope climbs and rock scrambles. The guide will assess the group fitness and the rope condition before continuing. The seventh falls is the highest cascade in the system, deep into the foothills, and the round trip from the third falls takes another four to five hours. Plan an early start if you intend to go that high.</p>
<h2>What to Bring</h2>
<ul>
<li>Trail runners with grip for wet rocks</li>
<li>Quick-dry shirt and shorts, the swim is part of the plan</li>
<li>Dry bag for the phone, wallet, and a spare shirt</li>
<li>Gloves for the rope sections above the third falls</li>
<li>Three liters of water for the climb to the third falls, four if going higher</li>
<li>Packed lunch for the third falls pool</li>
<li>Headlamp, the late descent can run into shadow</li>
<li>Cash for registration, guide, and the post-trek Kawa</li>
</ul>
<h2>The Trek-and-Kawa Combo</h2>
<p>The standard day plan is a 6 a.m. start, third falls by 9 a.m., swim and lunch until 11 a.m., back at the jump-off by 1 p.m., Kawa hot bath at 2 p.m., and dinner at the river-side carinderia by 5 p.m. The hot soak after the trek loosens the legs better than any stretching routine. The local Antique kitchens serve good chicken inasal and Antique-style kinilaw.</p>
<h2>Getting to Tibiao</h2>
<p>Fly to Caticlan or Iloilo, then drive to Tibiao. The drive from Caticlan is around three hours south through Pandan and Sebaste. The drive from Iloilo is around four and a half hours north through San Jose and Sibalom. <a href="https://www.cebupacificair.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">Cebu Pacific</a> serves both airports.</p>
<h2>When to Go</h2>
<p>November to May are the dry months and the safer trekking window. The rope sections above the third falls are easier with the lower water. June to October the falls run heavier and the photos are dramatic, but the descent is slicker and the higher falls may be closed by the local guide. The wet season gives the cleanest pool refills.</p>
<h2>Where to Stay</h2>
<p>The Kawa Hot Bath complex has rustic rooms, the Tibiao town has small farm stays and inns, and the Mararison Island ports up in Culasi have small lodges. Compare options on <a href="https://www.tripadvisor.com.ph/Hotels-g3895061-Antique_Province_Western_Visayas_Visayas-Hotels.html" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">TripAdvisor PH</a>.</p>
<p>The Tuburan seven-falls trek is the kind of day that pays back the long drive to Antique. The pool at the third falls, the rope sections higher up, and the Kawa soak after make for a satisfying outdoor weekend. Pair with Tibiao kayak the day before and Mararison Island the day after for a full Antique loop.</p>
HTML,
        'meta_title' => 'Tuburan Seven Falls Trek, Tibiao Antique: Plan | Resort Guru PH',
        'meta_description' => 'A DIY trek plan for the Tuburan and Bugtong Bato Falls in Tibiao, Antique. Falls order, swim stops, gear, transport, and the Kawa combo.',
        'tags' => 'Tuburan Falls, Bugtong Bato, Tibiao, Antique, Seven Falls Trek',
        'cover_destination_key' => 'iloilo-city',
    ],

