        'source_image_url' => null,
        'title' => 'Malapascua Thresher Shark Dive: A Calm Read on the Monad Shoal',
        'slug' => 'malapascua-thresher-shark-dive-monad-shoal-calm-read',
        'excerpt' => 'Malapascua Island in northern Cebu is the only reliable place in the world to see thresher sharks on a daily dawn dive. Here is the calm read for the trip.',
        'content_html' => <<<'HTML'
<p>Malapascua Island sits off the northern tip of Cebu, a small bangka ride from Maya port. The island is the only reliable place in the world to see thresher sharks on a daily basis, and the dive site that delivers them is Monad Shoal, a sunken atoll around 30 meters deep and 20 minutes by boat from the island. The threshers visit Monad Shoal at dawn to be cleaned by the resident cleaner wrasses. Divers descend the wall, settle on the ledge at 23 meters, and wait. The sharks come within five to ten meters on a regular morning.</p>
<p>This is the calm read for the trip. The thresher dive is the headline, but the surrounding sites and the slow island life are what make a three-day Malapascua weekend worth the travel time. Tara, the kwento by section.</p>
<h2>The Thresher Dive Itself</h2>
<p>The boat leaves the dive shop at 5 a.m. while the sky is still dark. The thresher dive is one tank deep, at 23 to 28 meters, on the lip of the Monad Shoal cliff. The current is mild and the visibility is regularly 20 meters.</p>
<h3>The Cleaning Stations</h3>
<p>Monad Shoal has three known cleaning stations along the ledge. The dive guide positions the group around the stations and signals when a thresher approaches. The sharks are around three to five meters long, with the long upper tail fin that gives them their name.</p>
<h3>What You Will Do on the Dive</h3>
<p>Settle on the ledge, do not chase the sharks. The threshers spook fast and disappear into the deep. Stay low, breathe slow, and let the sharks come. The standard sighting is two to four sharks across a 45-minute dive. Photo work is hard, the depth and the available light demand a strobe or a powerful focus light.</p>
<h2>Other Malapascua Dives</h2>
<p>Once you have logged the thresher dive, the surrounding sites are worth the trip on their own.</p>
<h3>Gato Island</h3>
<p>A protected marine sanctuary 30 minutes east. The island has a swim-through tunnel at 12 meters and a soft coral garden on the south side. Whitetip reef sharks rest in the tunnel. The bat cave on the surface holds thousands of fruit bats.</p>
<h3>Lapus Lapus and Bantigue Wall</h3>
<p>Two reef walls on the south side of Malapascua itself. Pygmy seahorses, frogfish, and the regular Coral Triangle critters. Both sites are macro-friendly.</p>
<h3>Calanggaman Island</h3>
<p>Not technically a Malapascua site, but a long boat ride away. The island is a sandbar with two beaches, a snorkel reef, and a wall. The full-day trip is a calm break from the deep dives.</p>
<h2>What to Bring</h2>
<ul>
<li>A 3mm wetsuit, the dawn water feels cold even at 27 degrees</li>
<li>Dive computer with a backup</li>
<li>A surface marker buoy and a reel for the deep ascent</li>
<li>Camera with a focus light for the thresher photos</li>
<li>Warm layer for the early-morning boat ride</li>
<li>Sunscreen for the surface intervals on the island</li>
<li>A small dry bag for the wallet and phone on the boat</li>
</ul>
<h2>Getting to Malapascua</h2>
<p>Fly to Cebu with <a href="https://www.cebupacificair.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">Cebu Pacific</a> or <a href="https://www.philippineairlines.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">Philippine Airlines</a>. From Cebu, a van or bus to Maya port takes around four hours along the northern Cebu coast. The bangka from Maya to Malapascua is 30 minutes; the last boat leaves around 4 p.m. Most dive shops include the airport transfer in the package.</p>
<h2>When to Go</h2>
<p>The threshers visit Monad Shoal year-round. The cleaner sightings stay consistent across the months. The dive weather is best from November to May, the dry months. June to October the typhoons can cancel the boat for a day or two but the island is sheltered enough that the dive sites stay open between storms. Peak diver season is March to May.</p>
<h2>Where to Stay</h2>
<p>Malapascua has a row of dive resorts and small inns along Bounty Beach on the south side. Compare options on <a href="https://www.tripadvisor.com.ph/Hotels-g946259-Malapascua_Island_Daanbantayan_Cebu_Island_Visayas-Hotels.html" target="_blank" rel="noopener nofollow">TripAdvisor PH</a>. Book the resort and the dive operator together; most resorts have their own boats.</p>
<p>Malapascua is the dive destination that earns its place on the global list. The threshers, the Gato tunnel, and the slow island days make for a trip that most divers leave already planning the next visit. For Philippine diving, this is the most reliable big-animal site in the country.</p>
HTML,
        'meta_title' => 'Malapascua Thresher Shark Dive: Monad Shoal Plan | Resort Guru PH',
        'meta_description' => 'A DIY plan for thresher shark diving at Monad Shoal off Malapascua Island, Cebu. Dawn dive, depth notes, side sites, transport, and best months.',
        'tags' => 'Malapascua, Thresher Shark, Monad Shoal, Cebu, Diving',
        'cover_destination_key' => 'cebu-city',
